# Inputs and outputs

## hemiconnectome.rds

Fisher-Z transformed connectivity values for all participants from the
resting-state data.

## hc_hpZ.rds

This is `hemiconnectome`, but normalized with-hemisphere, per participant,
i.e. `Z(FisherZ(r))`. "hpZ" stands for normalized within Hemisphere/Participant.

This is used to ask the questions:

 1. Can you predict hemisphere polarity from normalized connectomes?
 2. Can you predict hemisphere polarity from normalized connectomes when only
    one hemisphere from participant is included ("1p")?

## hemiconnectome_LL/RR

Correlation matrices generated from parcellations where the LH ROIs were
flipped onto the RH (LL) and RH ROIs flipped onto the LH (RR). Used to
investigate whether the classifier success is due to asymmetries in the
underlying parcellation.

## Directories

**03-right_handed**: Run the models on the right-handed participants.

**03-left_handed**: Run the models on the left-handed participants *and* the
matched right-handed participants.

**04-dim_reduce**: Run the dimension-reduction algorithm on the lefties,
righties and matched-righty groups.
